      ],
      "skos:definition": {
        "@value": "vector (<<iso80000-2>>) quantity giving the rate of change of a position vector (<<t3-1.10>>)",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "skos:note": {
        "@value": "The velocity vector is given by:\n\n[stem%unnumbered]\n++++\nii(bb(sf(v))) = (\"d\"ii(sf(r)))/(\"d\"t)\n++++\n\nwhere stem:[ii(sf(r))] denotes the position vector (<<t3-1.10>>) and stem:[t] the duration (<<t3-9>>).\n\nWhen the general symbol stem:[ii(bb(sf(v)))] is not used for the velocity, the symbols stem:[ii(sf(u))], stem:[ii(sf(v))], stem:[ii(sf(w))] may be used for the components (<<iso80000-2>>) of the velocity.\n",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "isoiec80000:hasUnit": [
        {
          "@id": "isoiec80000:unit-m*s^-1"
        }
      ],
